articles.author: 3DNews
articles.title: Microsoft has released security patches that break something in Windows 11 and 10
articles.description: Microsoft released major updates last week with dozens of patches for its Windows 11 and Windows 10 operating systems. One of the patches was meant to fix a vulnerability found in the Windows kernel related to access to confidential information. However, installing the patch to fix this vulnerability may lead to new problems. Some users reported issues with their antivirus program blocking the launch of Chrome after installing the update, while others experienced very long installation times. Microsoft has acknowledged the problem and has disabled the updates by default, but users can enable them through the operating system registry.

articles.title: Slow counteroffensive of Ukraine. What are the plans of the warring parties? - BBC Russian service
articles.description: This article reports on the ongoing fighting between Ukrainian and Russian forces in the Zaporizhzhia and Donetsk regions. Ukrainian forces have made slow progress into Russian-held territory, but have managed to capture several towns and villages. The situation remains tense, with both sides claiming significant losses and the Russian army attempting to counterattack. The article also includes estimates of the equipment losses suffered by both sides.

articles.author: Фонтанка.Ру
articles.title: Russian "Green Cards" will cease to be valid on June 30 - June 20, 2023 - Fontanka.Ru
articles.description: This article reports that Russian insurers can no longer issue "Green Cards" to drivers for travel to all countries in the system, and already issued policies will expire on June 30, 2023. Instead, Russia intends to create a new system with friendly countries called the "Blue Card." The RSA and the Belarusian insurance bureau have also signed an agreement on a single OSAGO policy similar to the "Green Card."

articles.author: Кубанские Новости
articles.title: How the Day of Memory and Sorrow will be held in Krasnodar - Kuban News
articles.description: On June 22nd, at 12:15 pm, all TV and radio stations, shopping centers, businesses, and train stations in Krasnodar will pause for one minute to remember the millions who died during World War II. Drivers of all types of vehicles can join the action by stopping and sounding their horns. This year marks the 82nd anniversary of the start of the war. Various events, such as lighting electronic candles and laying flowers at war memorials, will take place throughout the region.

articles.author: Новости Челябинска – 74.ru
articles.title: A bathyscaphe with tourists disappeared in the Atlantic Ocean - June 20, 2023
articles.description: A submarine named OceanGate, carrying two crew members and three tourists, including British billionaire Himish Harding, has gone missing in the Atlantic Ocean while exploring the wreckage of the Titanic. The submarine lost contact about an hour and 45 minutes after it submerged. The search and rescue operation is underway, and experts suggest that the submarine may have lost contact with the surface or may have gotten stuck in the Titanic wreckage. The submarine has a 96-hour oxygen supply for five people.

articles.author: 3DNews
articles.title: The YandexGPT neural network became available to third-party developers - 3DNews
articles.description: Yandex has announced that its neural network YandexGPT, also known as YaLM 2.0, is now available to third-party developers on the Yandex Cloud platform. Companies can apply to use the neural network to create their own chatbots, smart assistants, text processing, and solve various business tasks. The platform offers two modes: YandexGPT Playground and YandexGPT API. Playground is designed for testing the neural network to solve business problems, while YandexGPT API allows the service to be integrated into applications in test mode. The first users will be able to test the neural network in solving business tasks starting from July 2023.
